{"id":38726,"title":"John Langdon Down: Down's syndrome.","abstract":"When I was a medical student in the 1940's we youngsters were well familiar with the condition called 'Mongolism'. We saw these patients--labelled 'Mongols'--as children in the paediatric clinics, and as older patients on our visits to the local enormous mental hospital during our attachment in psychiatry, where many of them spent the whole of their lives.","date":"2014-01-10","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24404709","annotations":[{"name":"Down syndrome","weight":0.883265,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Down_syndrome"},{"name":"Pediatrics","weight":0.79024,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pediatrics"},{"name":"Medicine","weight":0.750806,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medicine"},{"name":"Psychiatric hospital","weight":0.735007,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychiatric_hospital"},{"name":"Psychiatry","weight":0.722145,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychiatry"},{"name":"Attachment theory","weight":0.273712,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Attachment_theory"},{"name":"Mind","weight":0.150554,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mind"},{"name":"John Langdon Down","weight":0.136412,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Langdon_Down"},{"name":"Student","weight":0.135236,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Student"},{"name":"Syndrome","weight":0.135186,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syndrome"},{"name":"Medical school","weight":0.131728,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical_school"},{"name":"Hospital","weight":0.120374,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hospital"},{"name":"Old age","weight":0.0805305,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_age"},{"name":"Clinic","weight":0.0805305,"w